How does thin computing address education-specific challenges?
A. by enabling the school IT department to run applications internally
B. by allowing school administrators to pay for actual application usage on a subscription
basis
C. by increasing interactive learning while budgets are being cut
D. by automatically implementing software upgrades and patches to keep content current
Answer: C
Explanation: The question is asking about education specific challenges in terms of thin
computing. Thin clients are cheap and easy to use, hence, option C is the right answer.
How should you present thin computing to your customers?
A. as a set of product offerings
B. as a user-customizable solution
C. as a full-function computer infrastructure
D. as a business solution
Answer: D
Where do the data and applications reside in a thin client solution?
A. on the Internet
B. on a cluster of servers
C. on the client
D. in the data center
Answer: B

Which advantages do thin clients offer in the financial industry?
A. Large computational capabilities support comples financial modeling.
B. Centralization of data in the data center satisfies regulatory and security requirements.
C. Support for rich multimedia applications provides real-time performance enhancements.
D. Instantaneous failover capabilities ensure maximum uptime.
Answer: B
How does thin computing help a customer who is facing increasing costs for hardware,
software updates, and maintenance?
A. Thin client solutions eliminate the cost of licensing and patch fixes.
B. Thin client solutions centralize the update, refresh, and maintenance processes in the
data center.
C. Thin client computing allows enormous computing tasks to be distributed among many
computers.
D. Thin clients allow customers to be responsible for administering their own updates,
refreshes, and maintenance.
Answer: B
Which need would motivate a customer to deploy a client virtualization solution?
A. to perform massive computational requirements
B. to eliminate of all single points of failure
C. to reduce desktop deployment costs and simplify management
D. to provide access for employees aby where there is Internet connectivity
Answer: C
